author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has signaled he intends to deploy the National Guard to other US cities after doing so in Los Angeles earlier this summer, and Washington, DC. CNN Senior Legal Analyst Elie Honig explains the legal hurdles the president may face. #CNN #News
title: Can Trump deploy the National Guard to other cities?

author: CNN
description:
A “network security incident” that forced Nevada state government offices to close this week and shut down some state websites and phone lines is the result of a cyberattack, Gov. Joe Lombardo said Tuesday.

“The incident is under active state and federal investigation,” a statement from Lombardo’s office said.

CNN's Fredricka Whitfield speaks with cybersecurity journalist Kim Zetter. #CNN #News
title: Nevada recovering after cyberattack incident closed government offices for days

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Nick Watt sits down with Matt Bowyer, the bookmaker at the center of the gambling scandal involving LA Dodgers star Shohei Ohtani’s interpreter. Bowyer reveals the world of high-stakes betting and opens up about life as a so-called “whale gambler.”
title: Ohtani Interpreter’s bookie: His life as a whale gambler

author: CNN
description: Ahead of this year’s U.S. college football season, SEC players weighed in on Love Island and which teammates might be the ideal bombshell to enter the villa. #CNN #News
title: SEC football players talk Love Island

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump’s anti-crime and clean-up efforts in Washington, DC have pushed the homeless population out of encampments, leaving many desperately searching for answers. Here is how some of the Capitol’s unhoused residents are reacting to the enforcement. #CNN #News
title: Homeless react to Trump's DC federal takeover

author: CNN
description:
Missouri Gov. Mike Kehoe on Friday announced a special session to draw new congressional maps – becoming the latest governor of a Republican-run state to accede to President Donald Trump’ s demands to undertake mid-decade redistricting.

Kehoe ordered lawmakers to return to the state capitol next week to take up the map-drawing, along with legislation aimed at weakening the state’s citizen initiative process.

CNN's Fredricka Whitfield speaks with Marina Jenkins, executive director of the National Democratic Redistricting Committee. #cnn  #News
title: Missouri governor calls special redistricting session amid Trump pressure

author: CNN
description: A federal appeals court said President Donald Trump’s unlawfully leaned on emergency powers to impose tariffs. The tariffs remain in place for now, after the court delayed implementation of its order until October. CNN’s Katelyn Polantz explains the details of this decision. #CNN #News
title: Federal appeals court strikes down many Trump tariffs

author: CNN
description: CNN's Victor Blackwell discusses with his "First of All" panel: Leo Smith, former minority engagement director of the Georgia GOP, former Atlanta mayor Kasim Reed and Jason "Jah" Lee, senior editor of Bossip. #CNN #News
title: Trump blasts cities over crime, yet admin has cut gun violence prevention funding

author: CNN
description:
Ukraine said its armed forces used cheap drones and Moscow’s mines to strike two bridges inside Russia, in a rare piece of good news for Kyiv. The bridges, near the border with Ukraine’s Kharkiv region, had strategic importance. Russia did not comment on the attacks.

#CNN #News #Ukraine #Russia
title: Ukraine strikes key Russian bridges

author: CNN
description: New Orleans musician Michael Harris looks back on Hurricane Katrina, twenty years later. He speaks with CNN's Randi Kaye. #CNN #News
title: Musician remembers 'the smell of death in the air' 20 years after Hurricane Katrina

author: CNN
description:
The month before a shooter opened fire on children gathered in a Minnesota church this week, the Trump administration cut funding in the state for efforts to identify potential mass shooters and head off their violence. 

The grants were ended as part of $18.5 million in cuts to a Homeland Security program that the Trump administration decried as partisan and unsuccessful — but which some experts and lawmakers say bolsters work to spot early warning signs of mass shooters like Robin Westman, who died of self-inflicted wounds after killing two children and wounding 18 others at a Catholic Mass on Wednesday.

CNN's Victor Blackwell speaks with former Minnesota Senate minority leader Melisa López Franzen. #cnn  #News
title: DHS cut funding to mass shooting prevention programs in Minnesota before shooting

author: CNN
description:
After backing away from a controversial logo rebrand loudly opposed by many right-wing influencers, Cracker Barrel also quietly made changes to its website this week. The Tennessee-based roadside restaurant chain deleted a dedicated “Pride page” and scrubbed references to employee resource groups, including its LGBTQ+ and Diversity, Equity, Inclusion and Belonging groups, from another part of its website. 

“On behalf of Cracker Barrel’s LGBTQ+ Alliance & DEIB Team, we want to celebrate YOU for being YOU. It is our greatest Mission to ensure that Pleasing People means ‘all people,’” Cracker Barrel’s now-deleted Pride page read, according to a CNN review of the Wayback Machine.

CNN business and tech writer Claire Duffy reports. #CNN #News
title: Cracker Barrel quietly removes DEI, Pride pages from its website after logo upheaval

author: CNN
description: Protests erupted in multiple cities as tensions soared across Indonesia, after a delivery rider was allegedly run over by a police armored vehicle during clashes between riot police and students protesting against lawmakers’ allowances. Three people died after protesters set fire to a regional parliament building, according to a Reuters report citing authorities. #CNN #News #Indonesia
title: Tensions soar in Indonesia as protests spread

author: CNN
description: The Pentagon is re-installing a portrait of Confederate General Robert E. Lee with a slave in the background at the West Point library. Republican Joe Borelli says imagery of the South evokes a certain history and ancestry of some Americans. Jennifer Welch says she doesn’t care and that if her ancestors owned slaves, “eff them.” #CNN #News
title: Podcast host: If my ancestors owned slaves, ‘eff them’

author: CNN
description: As world leaders begin to arrive in China’s Tianjin for the Shanghai Cooperation Organization summit, CNN’s Ivan Watson takes a look at how President Donald Trump is pushing many countries closer to China. #CNN #News #China
title: How Trump drives countries into China’s orbit

author: CNN
description: Geneva Cunningham, who was only 9-years-old when she survived the 2012 mass shooting at Sandy Hook Elementary School, shares her message to children who survived the mass shooting at a Catholic school in Minneapolis.
title: Sandy Hook survivor's message to kids in Minneapolis shooting

author: CNN
description: CNN's Erin Burnett speaks with Illinois Democratic Lt. Gov. Juliana Stratton about President Donald Trump calling for the deployment of National Guard troops in major US cities.
title: 'Wannabe dictator': Illinois Lt. Gov. Rips Trump's Chicago Crackdown

author: CNN
description: An emergency court hearing over President Donald Trump’s attempt to fire Federal Reserve Governor Lisa Cook ended with no immediate ruling from the judge overseeing the high-stakes legal battle. US District Judge Jia Cobb spent more than two hours Friday morning hearing arguments over Cook’s request to keep her job on the prominent board while her legal challenge plays out. #CNN #News
title: Court holds emergency hearing on firing of Federal governor

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration is preparing to conduct a major immigration enforcement operation in Chicago as soon as next week, according to multiple sources familiar with the planning, marking the latest escalation between the president and a Democratic-led city. #CNN #News
title: Officials: Trump admin could use Navy base for Chicago crackdown

author: CNN
description: Hillary McAfee sends her two children to elementary school with bulletproof shields due to the increase in school shooting threats.
title: Mother sends her children to school with ballistic shields
